CLOSING: TIER 2 IS WHERE MUSLIMS BECOME BUILDERSTier 2 (Sprint) is not another learning experience. It's the transformation tier.Where ideas become reality.\uc0\u8232 Where vague goals become specific commitments.\u8232 Where Muslims discover they CAN do hard things when they have crew.Where accountability stops being external judgment and becomes internal discipline born from peer commitment.Where Tawakkul (action + trust) is lived, not just talked about.This is the gold standard for accountability groups. This is what high-performing looks like. This is Tier 2.APPENDIX: QUICK REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATION CHECKLISTPre-Launch (Week 0)	\'95	Recruit and train first Captains	\'95	Build squad matching algorithm	\'95	Create pre-sprint survey template	\'95	Set meeting times (accommodate timezones)	\'95	Create Discord squad channels	\'95	Draft Captain onboarding training	\'95	Set up post-sprint surveySprint Launch (Week 1)	\'95	Inaugural 75-minute squad meeting	\'95	Ensure Captain opens with warmth (Islamic register)	\'95	Conduct goal clarity workshop	\'95	Run commitment ceremony	\'95	Confirm logistics (times, platform, access)Ongoing (Weeks 1-7)	\'95	Monday goal declarations (45-60 min)	\'95	Wednesday mid-week check-ins (45-60 min)	\'95	Friday end-of-week reflections (45-60 min)	\'95	Week 3: Special 90-minute midpoint ceremony	\'95	Monitor attendance and engagement	\'95	Collect weekly feedback signalsMonth 1	\'95	Post-sprint survey (all members)	\'95	Captain debrief meeting	\'95	Review goal achievement data	\'95	Analyze cohesion signals	\'95	Identify Captains for next cohort	\'95	Collect testimonials for marketingOngoing	\'95	Monthly Captain check-in calls (with Lead Coach)	\'95	Quarterly Captain trainings	\'95	Track key metrics (NPS, retention, extension rate)	\'95	Continuous improvement based on feedback}